Rambus Inc. Key Developments

Rambus Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for the Third Quarter of 2017 and Capital Expenditure Guidance for the Year 2017
Jul 24 17
Rambus Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported total revenue of $94,720,000, operating income of $8,244,000, income before income taxes of $5,112,000, net income of $2,605,000 or $0.02 per diluted share, non-GAAP operating income of $25,393,000, non-GAAP income before income taxes of $24,035,000, non-GAAP net income of $15,623,000 or $0.14 per diluted share compared to the total revenue of $76,501,000, operating income of $12,008,000, income before income taxes of $9,983,000, net income of $3,876,000 or $0.03 per diluted share, non-GAAP operating income of $25,998,000, non-GAAP income before income taxes of $25,648,000, non-GAAP net income of $16,671,000 or $0.15 per diluted share for the same quarter a year ago. EBITDA was $22,024,000 compared to $23,156,000 a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was $28,723,000 compared to $28,994,000 a year ago. 

For the year to date, the company reported total revenue of $192,071,000, operating income of $21,678,000, income before income taxes of $15,494,000, net income of $5,611,000 or $0.05 per diluted share, non-GAAP operating income of $55,992,000, non-GAAP income before income taxes of $53,331,000, non-GAAP net income of $34,665,000 or $0.30 per diluted share compared to the total revenue of $149,183,000, operating income of $21,302,000, income before income taxes of $16,378,000, net income of $5,754,000 or $0.05 per diluted share, non-GAAP operating income of $49,683,000, non-GAAP income before income taxes of $48,085,000, non-GAAP net income of $31,255,000 or $0.28 per diluted share for the same period a year ago.

For the third quarter of 2017, the company expected GAAP and Non-GAAP revenue to be between $96 million and $102 million, GAAP total operating costs and expenses revenue to be between $89 million and $85 million, Non-GAAP total operating costs and expenses revenue to be between $71 million and $67 million, GAAP operating income to be between $7 million and $17 million, Non-GAAP operating income to be between $25 million and $35 million, GAAP diluted net income per share to be between $0.02 and $0.08, Non-GAAP diluted net income per share to be between $0.14 and $0.20 and tax rate of 35%.

For the year 2017, the company expects roughly $8 million of CapEx for the year, with another $4 million or so in the second half.


